Gingery Carrot Cake with Pistachios gf
  --Aran Goyoaga

Cake:
3/4 c shelled pistachios
1 c (4 oz/113 g) blanched, finely ground almond flour
1/3 c (1 1/3 oz/38 g) cornstarch
1/2 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp baking soda
1/2 tsp salt
1/4 tsp ground cardamon
1 1/2 c shredded carrots (~2 carrots)
3 large eggs, beaten
3/4 c packed (5 1/4 oz/149 g) brown sugar
1/3 c evoo
1 tbsp grated fresh ginger

Adjust oven rack to middle position and heat oven to 350F. Make parchment sling for 8" square baking pan. Greash parchment. Pulse pistachios in food processor until finely ground, 10-15 pulses (it's ok if there are a few larger pieces). Measure out and reserve 1/4 c for garnish; transfer remainning to large bowl. Add almond flour, cornstarch, baking powder, baking soda, ground ginger, salt, and cardamon to bowl with pistachios, whisking to combine. Add carrots, eggs, sugar, oil, and grated ginger to pistachio misture, whisking to until smooth. Scrape batter into prepared pan, smoothing top with silicone spatula. Bake until toothpick inserted in middle of cake comes out clean, ~30 min, rotating pan halfway through. Let acke cool in pan on wire rack for 15 min. Left cake out pan, let cool completely, ~1 hr. 

Frosting:
8 oz (227 g) cream cheese, softened
7 tbsp (99 g) unsalted butter, softened
1/2 c (2 oz/57 g) confectioners' sugar
1 tsp vanilla
1/4 tsp salt

Using stand miser with paddle attachment, beat cream cheese and butter on medium until well combined and creamy, ~2 min. Add sugar and vanilla and beat on low speed until incorporated, ~30 s. Spread frosting evenly over top of cooled cake, then sprinkle with reserved pistachios. Cake can be refrigerated for up to 3 days, bring to room temp before service.

